-- Sidecar raises $15 mln from investors including Richard Branson
-- 
-- Mon Sep 15, 2014 03:05PM EDT
-- None



Sept 15 (Reuters) - Sidecar, a ride-sharing startup which competes with on-demand car services such as Uber and Lyft, said it raised $15 million from existing and new investors, including Virgin Group founder Richard Branson.

Existing investors Avalon Ventures and Union Square Ventures also participated in the funding round, the company wrote in a blog post. (http://bit.ly/X7doo8)